The paper proposes a deep learning approach for land cover segmentation using remote sensing data. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The approach also involves the use of uncertainty measures and memory gates, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of memory gates suggests a potential application of recurrent neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of remote sensing data, which could also fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
